Teamwork/communication: weak leadership, arrogance may hinder crew cooperation. Professional development: not mentioned.\n\nNow weigh for long-distance pilot: need high reliability, technical competence, calm under pressure, good decision-making, teamwork/communication crucial for crew. Also professional development for long-term.\n\nC has reliability, good decision-making, positive atmosphere, but communication difficulty and unwillingness to further education. Egocentric may affect crew. B has good stress handling but poor teamwork. D has strong technical and decision-making, but poor leadership and arrogance may affect crew. A lacks info on calmness and teamwork.\n\nThus likely best candidate is C? Because reliability, decision-making, positive atmosphere outweigh communication difficulty? But communication difficulty is a significant issue for pilot. However \"difficulty communicating ideas\" could be mitigated? But we must not infer mitigation. It's a weakness. Egocentric also negative. Not willing to further education is a long-term issue.\n\nD has strong technical and decision-making, but arrogance and weak leadership may be serious for crew. However he takes responsibility seriously, which is good. No explicit communication weakness, but weak leadership may affect teamwork.\n\nB has conscientiousness and stress handling, but nasty remarks and uncooperative are strong negatives for crew.\n\nA lacks calmness info, unorganized, poor at criticism.\n\nThus likely D or C. Need decide. Considering long-distance flights require calmness under pressure, technical problem solving, decision-making, and responsibility. D shows those strengths. Teamwork is weaker but not explicitly negative except arrogance and weak leadership. C has strong reliability and positive atmosphere but communication difficulty and unwillingness to develop may be problematic for long-term.\n\nThus I lean toward D as best overall, given technical competence and calmness, responsibility. The leadership weakness may be mitigated but still a concern. However C's communication difficulty may be more severe for safety. So choose D.\n\nNow produce public message summarizing evaluation and vote for D."}
