w\u2011it\u2011all\u201d and has a hot temper \u2013 traits that can undermine crew interaction and teamwork.\n- *Missing evidence*: no explicit description of his communication style or concrete examples of crew interaction.\n### Weighing the criteria\n| Criterion | Who meets it best? | Key trade\u2011offs |\n|-----------|-------------------|----------------|\n| Reliability / Responsibility | **C** (explicit 100\u202f% reliability) \u2013 D also takes responsibility seriously, B is very conscientious. |\n| Technical & Cognitive Competence | **D** (problem\u2011solving, concentration, handling unexpected events) \u2013 A also strong in situational awareness, B good at weather assessment. |\n| Calmness & Judgment under Pressure | **D** (adequate response to unexpected events, strong concentration) \u2013 B handles stress well; C\u2019s quick decisions imply calmness but are not explicit. |\n| Decision\u2011making | **C** (quick correct decisions) \u2013 D (problem solving, response to events). |\n| Teamwork & Communication | **C** (creates a positive crew atmosphere) \u2013 A has leadership but is unfriendly; B\u2019s interpersonal record is largely negative; D\u2019s arrogance, weak leadership and loner reputation are serious concerns. |\n| Professional Development / Long\u2011term Suitability | **C** has a noted reluctance to further education (negative); others have no explicit data either way. |\n### Overall assessment\n- **Candidate\u202fD** excels technically and in calm decision\u2011making, but his interpersonal profile (arrogance, weak leadership, moody, loner) poses a substantial risk for crew coordination on long\u2011haul flights where teamwork is essential.\n- **Candidate\u202fB** is reliable and stress\u2011resilient but has clear, documented hostility toward colleagues, which would erode crew trust.\n- **Candidate\u202fA** shows strong situational awareness and leadership potential, yet we have no evidence of calmness under pressure and his unfriendly, unorganized demeanor could hinder crew interaction.\n- **Candidate\u202fC** combines perfect reliability, rapid correct decision\u2011making, excellent attention, and a proven ability to foster a positive crew atmosphere. The only downsides are communication difficulty, an egocentric streak, and a lack of enthusiasm for further education\u2014issues that, while important, are less likely to jeopardize immediate flight safety than the overt interpersonal deficits seen in B and D.\nGiven the balance of strengths and weaknesses, **Candidate\u202fC** appears to be the best overall fit for a long\u2011distance pilot role: he is fully reliable, makes sound decisions quickly, maintains crew morale, and possesses the cognitive skills needed for complex, extended operations. The communication weakness is a concern, but it is offset by his positive impact on crew atmosphere and his strong reliability.\n**My vote:** Candidate C\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}"}
